{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Established in 2007, its goal is to 'make wholesale extraction, transformation, and analysis of open web data accessible to researchers' [8].",
    "The released datasets comprise the world's largest free, multilingual corpus of scraped web data [2], estimated to contain about 250 billion pages (over 9.5 petabytes), with between 3 and 5 billion pages added each month [8].",
    "Due to the dataset's scale, it is sometimes incorrectly described as containing 'the entire web'.",
    "As Baack [2] points out, it is not even a representative sample of the web.New CC releases are published every one-two months, and are freely available via S3 and HTTP protocols 11.",
    "Each release is divided into 300 Web Archive (WARC) chunks for easier access, and accompanied by the index with relevant metadata on each web document, such as the web document's original URL, MIME-type, and content length."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Established in 2007, its goal is to 'make wholesale extraction, transformation, and analysis of open web data accessible to researchers' [8].",
    "The released datasets comprise the world's largest free, multilingual corpus of scraped web data [2], estimated to contain about 250 billion pages (over 9.5 petabytes), with between 3 and 5 billion pages added each month [8].",
    "As Baack [2] points out, it is not even a representative sample of the web.New CC releases are published every one-two months, and are freely available via S3 and HTTP protocols 11."
